INSERT INTO `cmsinfo` (`order`, `title`, `content`, `update_at`, `created_at`, `permalink`, `id`) VALUES
(0, 'Home', '<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><span style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; font-size: 12px; font-weight: bold;">Image Upload Enhancements</span></p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">I have added image uploading capabilities to this CMS. These are the steps I followed.</p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Setup:</strong></p>\r\n<ol style="padding: 0em 0em 0em 1.5em; margin: 0em 0em 1.5em; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Decide to add image upload enhancements to this blog.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Re-read my<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://connect.rrc.ca/DACCA/INFSF/COMP-2459/Shared%20Documents/code%20examples/upload.zip">image upload demo code</a>.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Prepare file-system by creating an "uploaded_images" folder within the root folder of this project.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Add required "enctype" attribute to my new/edit forms.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Add input of type "file" to this form as well.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Create the images table.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Alter the pages table to include an "image_id" column.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Test page creation/update to ensured that I didn''t break anything with the above changes.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Associating an Image with a Page:</strong></p>\r\n<ol style="padding: 0em 0em 0em 1.5em; margin: 0em 0em 1.5em; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Modify the create process such that the uploaded image is moved to the uploaded_images folder once it is uploaded.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">After the image is moved, insert its details (filename, mimetype, height, width) into the images table.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Use my mysqli object to find the id of the images row I just created. (<a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://ca.php.net/manual/en/mysqli.insert-id.php">$mysql-&gt;insert_id</a>)</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Create the new page with the POSTed data as usual. If an image was uploaded set the page''s image_id column to the id acquired in the previous step.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Repeat steps 4 through 12 for the edit/update process.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Display an Image within a Page:</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Loading a page with an image will either require two queries, or better yet one query with a<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://www.codinghorror.com/blog/2007/10/a-visual-explanation-of-sql-joins.html">LEFT OUTER JOIN</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">For example, a query for a page (primary key = 7) might end up looking like this. (A select based on the permalink would be similar except for the where clause.)</p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">SELECT * FROM cms_pages<br style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;" />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; LEFT OUTER JOIN images ON cms_pages.image_id = images.image_id<br style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;" />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; WHERE cms_pages.id = 7;</p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><em style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Note: I realize now that the id column in the images table should be called image_id, otherwise the two tables we are joining will have identically named primary keys.</em></p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">I''m displaying the image below the content all pages. If the width of the image (stored in the images table) is greater than my content area I apply a width attribute to the img tag.</p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Dissociating&nbsp;an Image with a Page:</strong></p>\r\n<ol style="padding: 0em 0em 0em 1.5em; margin: 0em 0em 1.5em; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Modify the edit form such that we load the required page using a LEFT OUTER JOIN with the images table.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">When creating the edit form check if an image is associated with our page. If so, display a thumbnail of the image instead of the &lt;input type="file" ... /&gt;.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">Below this thumbnail add a checkbox input to delete the image association.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">When processing the POST from this form look for the checkbox input name to be set in $_POST. (Remember that checkboxes only appear in this hash if they are checked.)</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 5px;">If a delete checkbox is detected set the image_id column of the page to NULL.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><span style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; font-size: 12px; font-weight: bold;">Previous Work on CMS</span></p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">My example CMS is a work in progress. As the site is developed I will update the lists below.</p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">You can add, edit and delete cms pages from the<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://stungeye.com/school/cms/admin.php">admin page</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Admin User: ghostface<br style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;" />Admin Password: killa&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em 0em 1em; line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><span style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; font-size: 12px; font-weight: bold;">Previous To Do List</span></p>\r\n<ul style="padding: 0em 0em 0em 1.5em; margin: 0em 0em 1.5em; color: #333333; font-family: georgia,''times new roman'',serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Build XHTML template for site.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Add CSS to style site template</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Build XHTML/CSS for<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://stungeye.com/school/cms/admin.php">Admin page</a></li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Build XHTML/CSS for<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://stungeye.com/school/cms/admin.php">New page</a></li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Create CMS pages table.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Add TinyMCE to enabled WYSIFYG forms</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Add some progressive enhancements using<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://stungeye.com/school/cms/js/main.js">JQuery</a></li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Create a page "Model".</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Implement page Creation(on<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://stungeye.com/school/cms/new.php">New page</a>)</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Implement page Listing (on<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://stungeye.com/school/cms/admin.php">Admin page</a>)</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Implement page Editing</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Implement page Deletion (on<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em; color: #b96d00; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://stungeye.com/school/cms/admin.php">Admin page</a>)</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Ensure that created_at/updated_at columns are working as required.</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Implement page loading via permalink URLS</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Implement dynamic menu via permalinks/titles</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Enable home page content selection (via ''home'' permalink)</li>\r\n<li style="padding: 0em; margin: 0em;">Enable HTTP Authentication</li>\r\n</ul>', '2011-11-19 13:10:32', '2011-11-19 13:10:32', 'home', 7),
(0, 'Our Products', '<table class="title-wrapper" style="margin-top: 45px; margin-right: 385px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; padding: 0px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: small;">\r\n<h2 style="font-size: 35px !important; margin-top: 0px !important; margin-right: 0px !important; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px !important; font-family: Arial, sans-serif !important; font-weight: normal !important; white-space: nowrap !important; line-height: 42px !important;">Technical Details</h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr class="Teq-technical-details-inbox">\r\n<td style="font-size: small;">\r\n<div class="Teq-technical-details-info">\r\n<table id="technical-details-table" style="margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px !important;" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="10" width="100%">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Display</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">Amazon''s 6" diagonal most advanced E Ink display, optimized with proprietary waveform and font technology, 600 x 800 pixel resolution at 167 ppi, 16-level gray scale.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Size (in inches)</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">6.5" x 4.5" x 0.34" (166 mm x 114 mm x 8.7 mm)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Weight</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">5.98 ounces (170 grams)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>System Requirements</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">None, because it''s wireless and doesn''t require a computer to download content.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>On-device Storage</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">Up to 1,400 books or 2GB internal (approximately 1.25GB available for user content).</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Cloud Storage</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">Free cloud storage for all Amazon content.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Battery Life</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">A single charge lasts up to one month with wireless off based upon a half-hour of daily reading time. Keep wireless always on and it lasts for up to 3 weeks. Battery life will vary based on wireless usage, such as shopping the Kindle Store, web browsing, and downloading content.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Charge Time</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">Fully charges in approximately 3 hours via the included USB 2.0 cable connected to a computer. U.S. power adapter sold separately.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Wi-Fi Connectivity</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">Supports public and private Wi-Fi networks or hotspots that use the 802.11b, 802.11g, or 802.11n standard with support for WEP, WPA and WPA2 security using password authentication or Wi-Fi Protected Setup (WPS); does not connect to WPA and WPA2 secured networks using 802.1X authentication methods; does not support connecting to ad-hoc (or peer-to-peer) Wi-Fi networks.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>USB Port</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">USB 2.0 (micro-B connector)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Content Formats Supported</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">Kindle (AZW), TXT, PDF, unprotected MOBI, PRC natively; HTML, DOC, DOCX, JPEG, GIF, PNG, BMP through conversion.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Documentation</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;"><a style="color: #004b91;" href="http://kindle.s3.amazonaws.com/KindleQuickStartGuide.pdf" target="_blank">Quick Start Guide</a>&nbsp;(included in box);&nbsp;<a style="color: #004b91;" href="http://kindle.s3.amazonaws.com/KindleUser%27sGuide.pdf" target="_blank">Kindle User''s Guide</a>&nbsp;(pre-installed on device). Additional information in multiple languages&nbsp;<a style="color: #004b91;" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=200399670" target="_blank">available online</a>.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Warranty and Service</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;"><a style="color: #004b91;" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=200728730" target="_blank">1-year limited warranty and service</a>&nbsp;included. Optional&nbsp;<a style="color: #004b91;" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0058WBTQO/ref=kinw4_ddp">2-year protection plan</a>&nbsp;available for U.S. customers sold separately. Use of Kindle is subject to the&nbsp;<a style="color: #004b91;" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=200699130" target="_blank">terms found here</a>.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; text-align: left;" width="20%" align="right" bgcolor="#EAF3FE"><strong>Included in the Box</strong></td>\r\n<td style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">Kindle wireless e-reader, USB 2.0 cable, and&nbsp;<a style="color: #004b91;" href="http://kindle.s3.amazonaws.com/KindleQuickStartGuide.pdf" target="_blank">Quick Start Guide</a>. Power adapter sold separately.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2011-11-19 14:13:49', '2011-11-19 14:13:49', 'products', 15),
